org.jsapar.parse

Class DocumentBuilderLineEventListener

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jsapar.parse.DocumentBuilderLineEventListener
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    AutoCloseable, EventListener, LineEventListener

    public class DocumentBuilderLineEventListener
extends Object
implements LineEventListener, AutoCloseable
    This line event listener can be used to build a document based on line events. Use this class only if you are sure that the whole file can be parsed into memory. If the file is too big, a OutOfMemory exception will be thrown. For large files use any of the ParseTask implementations directly instead. Dispose instances of this class when they have been used once.

        public Document getDocument()
